What's this LoRA

This is a LoRA trained on AI generated pictures with only two colors (made using the Bing Image Creator). My models are not trained to achieve the exact style of their source, but to change the general vibe of the image. They are also fine-tuned on anime models, so they may not work perfectly with realistic ones.

The images in the examples are created using only this LoRA and different models (mainly my custom):

Mitama Yakumo LyCORIS LoCon

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

CC License

A LYCORIS Locon of Mitama Yakmo from the spin-off Madoka series Magia Record: Puella Magi Madoka☆Magica Side Story.

You will have to install this extension made by KohakuBlueLeaf into your webui to fully use a LyCORIS Locon

https://github.com/KohakuBlueleaf/a1111-sd-webui-locon

This Locon was made with a collection of fanart images and a few screencaps from the gacha mobile game, she can be easily changed into multiple outfits and hairstyles as long as if you up the strength on the specific hairstyle and outfit you want to put her in (1.2-1.4 should be good enough) but yes you should always do your best to make Yui Horie voiced characters look pretty/cute in alternative outfits, that's the best thing about AI tbh

Compatibility

Trained on the NAI model, so it's pretty much compatible with every NAI based Anime model mix that you can find on the internet

Recommended Weight

Always 1.0 by itself and 0.8-0.7 if you're mixing it with other LORAs.

Trigger Tokens

normitama will be the token needed for her normal look, the additional tags needed to easily get her basic look will be

"long hair, single hair bun, ponytail, black ascot, bangs, blue eyes, blue skirt, large breasts, frills, grey hair, hair intakes, hair ornament, sleeveless, white gloves, blue tailcoat, blue vest, hair flower, blue rose, frills, black footwear"

you'll get her main look, the only thing that might not appear is the tailcoat or exact footwear but you'll get it with every batch so just keep on outputting, honestly not sure what's the reason for the tailcoat having RNG but it's probably because the training process and random cropping missed the few fanart pictures that had her fully showing off her outfit and tailcoat

mizumitama will be the token you use for her swimsuit outfit, the additional tags needed to generate this look will be

"large breasts, blue one-piece swimsuit, jewelry, blue eyes, blue rose, hair ornament, very long hair, o-ring, bracelet, necklace, braid, ring, grey hair, bangs, single braid, side braid, hair intakes"

newyearsmitama will be the token you use for her new years outfit, sadly not a lot of images were available to train this outfit so it isn't a 100% exact look to her new years costume but with the trigger token and additional tags you may get outputs that look close to it

"bangs, black footwear, black ribbon, blue eyes, blue kimono, blue rose, high heel boots, braid, floral print, frilled sleeves, frills, fur collar, fur trim, grey hair, hair flower, hair ribbon, long hair, long sleeves, obi, print kimono, sash, sidelocks, single side bun, white gloves, wide sleeves"

If you want to support me, like always just check my posted links here, I'll be thankful if you support me through all or one of my platforms and I'm looking forward to working on more LORAs o/
